{"lemma":"يابِسٌ","slug":"يابِسٌ","root":"#.ب.س","root_slug":"_-ب-س","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ب-س","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"يابِس","root":"يبس","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n42446"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B3%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"dry","examples":[{"text":"لَا تَكُنْ رَطْبًا فَتُعْصَرَ وَلَا يَابِسًا فَتُكْسَرَ.","english":"Be flexible, but firm; Like an egg, if it's held too tightly, it breaks, and if it's held too loosely, it will slip from grasp."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/jaː.bis/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n42446","headword_ar":"يَابِسٌ","root":"ybs","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dried up, after having been moist, humid, succulent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb, K:) or, [rather,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dried up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exsiccated:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also, [but perhaps tropically,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stiff, rigid, tough, firm, resisting pressure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see 1:] (M:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yub~asN","text_ar":"يُبَّسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabosN","text_ar":"يَبْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which latter is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakobN","text_ar":"رَكْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rAkibN","text_ar":"راكِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (ISk, S, Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yubosN","text_ar":"يُبْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a dial. form. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabosN","text_ar":"يَبْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A'Obeyd, S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabosN","text_ar":"يَبْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [rather] a quasi-pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaAbisN","text_ar":"يَابِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabasN","text_ar":"يَبَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) or this last is used by poetic license for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabosN","text_ar":"يَبْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) also, (S, M,) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabosN","text_ar":"يَبْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaAbisN","text_ar":"يَابِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabasN","text_ar":"يَبَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabisN","text_ar":"يَبِسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabiysN","text_ar":"يَبِيسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabowsN","text_ar":"يَبْوسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabaAsN","text_ar":"يَبَاسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayobasu","text_ar":"اَيْبَسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabasN","text_ar":"يَبَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry from its origin, not having been known moist:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) but ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabosN","text_ar":"يَبْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry after having been known to be moist:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and as to the path of Moses, [to which the former of the last two epithets is applied in the Kur. xx. 79,] it had never been known as a path either moist or dry, for God only showed it to them created such; but the epithet is also read with sukoon to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":", because, though it had not been a path, it was a place wherein had been water and which had dried up: (K, TA:) the latter reading is that of El-Hasan El-Basree: and El-Aamash read the word with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) Th [however] says, (S,) you say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaTabN yabosN","text_ar":"حَطَبٌ يَبْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry fire-wood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though it were so"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"naturally:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb:) [and J says,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabasN","text_ar":"يَبَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies a place"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry after having been moist;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so in the instance in the Kur. mentioned above: (S:) [and Fei says,] it signifies a place"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has had in it water which has gone away;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as Az says, a path"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is no moisture:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) [and ISd says,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabosN","text_ar":"يَبْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabas","text_ar":"يَبَس","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify a place that is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner, applied to land ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroD","text_ar":"اَرْض"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of which the water and pasturage have dried up:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter, so applied, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hard;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaAbisN","text_ar":"يَابِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  applied to a stone: (A:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabysN","text_ar":"يَبيسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is [generally] applied to a plant, or herbage, as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dry,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dried up;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, Msb, K;) as also [sometimes]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaAbisN","text_ar":"يَابِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, K;) the former being of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAEilN","text_ar":"فَاعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) or it is so applied to herbs, or leguminous plants, of the sort termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoraAr","text_ar":"اَحْرَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"[that are eaten without being cooked, or that are slender and succulent, &c.], (As, K,) and of the sort termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ukuwr","text_ar":"ذُكُور"},{"kind":"text","text":"[that are hard and thick, or thick and rough, &c.]; (As, TA;) and [so As, in the TA; and so in some copies of the K; but in the CK, or] those herbs and leguminous plants that become scattered when they dry up; (As, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yubosN","text_ar":"يُبْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabosN","text_ar":"يَبْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) but not to what is dry of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaliY~","text_ar":"حَلِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sil~iyaAn","text_ar":"صِلِّيَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Halamap","text_ar":"حَلَمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (As, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almafoluwju","text_ar":"المَفْلُوجُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlyaAbisu Al$~iq~i","text_ar":"اليَابِسُ الشِّقِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The palsied of whom the half is without sensation and without motion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN yaAbisN mina Als~ukori","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ يَابِسٌ مِنَ السُّكْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn) app. meaning (assumed tropical:)  A"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"man as though he were dead and dried up in consequence of much intoxication."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yAabisu AlT~abiyEapi","text_ar":"ياَبِسُ الطَّبِيعَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Costive."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakoraAnu yaAbisN","text_ar":"سَكْرَانُ يَابِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Intoxicated so much as not to speak;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though the wine had dried him up by its heat. (M.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ataAnN yabosapN","text_ar":"اَتَانٌ يَبْسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, M) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabasapN","text_ar":"يَبَسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, M) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A she-ass dry and lean."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aApN yabosN","text_ar":"شَاةٌ يَبْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabasN","text_ar":"يَبَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, S, M, K) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A ewe,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she-goat, without milk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, S, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whose milk has stopped, and her udder become dry."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imoraA^apN yabasapN","text_ar":"اـِمْرَاَةٌ يَبَسَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman who has no milk:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabasaAtN","text_ar":"يَبَسَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayobaAsN","text_ar":"اَيْبَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [quasi-pl. n.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaAbisN","text_ar":"يَابِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAmilN","text_ar":"جَامِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAqirN","text_ar":"بَاقِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA, from the Moheet.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiroqN yabiysN","text_ar":"عِرْقٌ يَبِيسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A dry duct"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"penis."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEarN yaAbisN","text_ar":"شَعَرٌ يَابِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hair upon which no effect is produced by moistening with water nor with oil;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA *;) which is the worst sort thereof. (TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabiysu AlmaA='i","text_ar":"يَبِيسُ المَا=ءِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dry sweat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A:) or [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sweat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, S, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN yaAbisN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ يَابِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabiysN","text_ar":"يَبِيسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man having little good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoroA^apN yaAbisapN","text_ar":"اِمْرْاَةٌ يَابِسَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabiysN","text_ar":"يَبِيسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabasN","text_ar":"يَبَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a woman having little good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in whom is no good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who does not cause one to obtain any good."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonahumaA varFY A^ayobasu","text_ar":"بَيْنَهُمَا ثَرًى اَيْبَسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Between them two is disunion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["A","Msb","K","M","ISk","S","TA","As","AHn","IAar","Th","AO"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}